observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the:
(a) LCE create an Inventory Committee composed of adequate number of personnel to be able to prepare the Physical Inventory Plan and complete the physical inventory in three months or less in adherence with COA Circular 2020-006.  The Inventory Committee are advised to follow the general and procedural guidelines stated in the said Circular including disposition and recording of the missing PPEs;
(b) Management to allocate fund for the expenses to secure copies of the title of the declared real properties and assigned a focal person who will focus on the requirements needed to facilitate the immediate transfer of titles of the parcels of land under the name of the Municipality;
(c)  Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to request and assign, as the case may be, personnel who will prepare and maintain updated property cards to enable reconciliation with the general ledger balances and the inventory report;
(d) Management to request for authority for the derecognition of missing items,  duly supported with appropriate documentation, if accountability/responsibility over the missing PPE could not be pinpointed after investigation as required under Section 7 of COA Circular 2020-006; and
(e) Municipal Accountant to identify semi-expendable property which were recognized as PPE and reclassify to the affected appropriate semi-expendable inventory accounts (if not yet issued to end-user), expense accounts (if issued within the year) or accumulated surplus/deficit/retained earnings accounts(if issued in prior years) consistent with Section 5.4 of COA Circular No. 2016-006.

We recommended the Management to fast track the filling up of the two (2) vacant positions in LDRRMO.


We recommended that the LDRRM Officer; 

a) observe the guidelines set by the higher authorities such as GPPB, DILG, DBM and COA in relation to provide measures in addressing the COVID-19 situation in the Municipality.

We recommended and Management agreed to 

(a) reconstitute the composition of the LGU GFPS- Execom and identify clearly the GAD Focal Person; 

(b)  submit a copy of the Annual GPB to the COA Audit Team within five (5) workings days from the receipt of the approved plan; 

(c) submit the annual GAD Accomplishment Report with the required documentswithin five (5) working days from the end of January of the preceding year; and 

(d)LCEidentify the Chairperson of GFPS -TWG through issuance of a Memorandum to lead the GAD Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) Team for proper evaluation of the results of the LGU’s GAD PPAs in accordance with the provisions of PCW/DILG/DBM/NEDA Joint Circular 2013-01.

We recommended that Management:
a) through the Solid Waste Management Board, encourage active participation of barangay officials to support the solid waste management program of the Municipality;
b) ensure full implementation/operation of the existing 14 barangays’ MRF to help in waste diversion of the Municipality;
c) continue all its efforts and initiative in maintaining the operations of a centralized MRF and plans and programs incorporated in its 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan in accordance with the RA No. 9003.

We recommended that the Management:
(a) reorganize the composition of the LGU GFPS- Execom in accordance with MCW-IRR;
(b)  submit a copy of the Annual GPB to the COA Audit Team within five (5) workings days from the receipt of the approved plan;
(c) submit the annual GAD Accomplishment Report with the required documentswithin five (5) working days from the end of January of the preceding year; and
(d)LCEidentify the Chairperson of GFPS -TWG through issuance of a Memorandum to lead the GAD Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) Team for proper evaluation of the results of the LGU’s GAD PPAs in accordance with the provisions of PCW/DILG/DBM/NEDA Joint Circular 2013-01.

We reiterated our prior year’s recommendation that the: 

(a) Local Chief Executive (i) create an inventory committee to conduct annual physical inventory of PPE by type, with the end view of establishing the correctness of the reported balances as well as the existence, condition and custodianship of the municipal assets and submit the RPCPPE not later than January 31 of each year to enable reconciliation with the accounting and property records; and 

(ii) allocate funds for the proper titling of all land declared in the name of the LGU; 

(b) Municipal Treasurer (i) prepare and maintain updated property cards to enable reconciliation with the general ledger balances; 

(c)  Municipal Accountant (i) maintain updated PPELC; and 

(d)  Municipal Treasurer, Assessor and Accountant exert effort to verify the existence of the title of the declared real properties and secure copies thereof.

We recommended that Management:

a) through the Solid Waste Management Board, encourage active participation of barangay officials to support the solid waste management program of the Municipality;

b) ensure full implementation/operation of the existing 14 barangays’ MRF to help in waste diversion of the Municipality;

c) continue all its efforts and initiative in maintaining the operations of a centralized MRF and plans and programs incorporated in its 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan in accordance with the RA No. 9003.

