We recommended and Management agreed to 

(a) LDRRM Officer prepare and monitor the full implementation of LDRRM plan towards the achievement of the objectives of RA No. 10121 and strictly comply with the requirements of COA Circular No. 2012-002 for the preparation and submission of the utilization report of LDRRM Fund to the Auditor every 15th day of each month for timely review and verification; 

(b) Municipal Accountant to submit the complete and original copy of the required supporting documents for the purchase and distribution of supplies;

We recommended and Management agreed  to strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 by 

(a) demand for the immediate settlement of all outstanding cash advances for which no liquidation report has been submitted;  


(b) file appropriate charges against officers for failure to liquidate the cash advances after purposes of the grant had been served; 

(c) fully liquidate all cash advances at the end of the year; and

We recommended  and Management agreed to  


(a) strictly comply on the required composition of SWMB for proper representation thereof; 







(b) conduct IEC to fully educate the barangays on the proper waste segregation; 

(c)  strictly enforce the garbage collectors to wear their personal protective gears to ensure their safety and protection and educate them on the health hazards of their job; and





(d) provide the COA-office of the final version of the plan with Resolution and annual progress report on strategies implemented as well as accomplishments received by  the  National Solid Waste Management Commission through its Secretariat.

